data.enText: intended to last for only a short time until sb/sth more permanent is found

data.chText: 过渡政府；临时措施 / 报告
在大选之前的过渡阶段由副总统执政。
data.enText: The vice-president took power in the interim period before the election.
calculated before the final results of sth are known

data.chText: 期中数字 / 利润 / 结果

data.enText: during the period of time between two events; until a particular event happens

data.chText: 不管在此间所发生的一切，他们还是好朋友。
data.enText: Despite everything that had happened in the interim, they had remained good friends.

data.chText: 她的新工作要到五月份才开始，在这期间她将继续原有的工作。
data.enText: Her new job does not start until May and she will continue in the old job in the interim.

tr: the time between one event, process, or period and another
example: meanwhile the socialists are running the government

tr: serving during an intermediate interval of time

value.def: Interim is used to describe something that is intended to be used until something permanent is done or established.

example.ex: She was sworn in as head of an interim government in March.
example.tran: 她3月份宣誓就任过渡政府首脑。

value.tran: 暂时的;临时的;过渡期间的

value.def: In the interim means until a particular thing happens or until a particular thing happened.

example.ex: But, in the interim, we obviously have a duty to maintain law and order...
example.tran: 但是,在过渡期间,我们显然有责任维护治安。

example.ex: He was to remain in jail in the interim.
example.tran: 他在此期间将会继续被关押。

trans: 中间报告；中期报告；临时报告；中期報告；中期财务报告
